<p>1.4 Our staff, contractors and agents have no authority to make individual exceptions or amendments to these terms and conditions.</p>
<p>1.5 In these terms and conditions we refer to various policies that we have established in connection with the operation of Cycle Hire.  These policies are available on request from us.</p>
<p>1.6 All personal data about you and any Additional User will be processed in accordance with our Privacy Notice, which will be presented for your review and acceptance before you submit any personal information to us.  Further information on how personal data is processed by us is available at <a href="/corporate/privacy-and-cookies/index">tfl.gov.uk/privacy</a>.</p>
<p>1.7 We may amend these terms and conditions, including the Charges, from time to time.  In these circumstances, you may be eligible for a refund of certain Charges that you have paid us in accordance with our Refund Policy.  A copy of the latest version of the terms and conditions can be obtained from <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/cycle-hire">tfl.gov.uk/cycle-hire</a> or are available on request from us.</p>
<h2>Registration</h2>
<p>2.1 To register as a Registered User or to use Cycle Hire as a Casual User, you must:</p>
<p>(a) be aged 18 years or over;<br />
(b)	ensure that all data provided by you is accurate;<br />
(c)	select a Bike Access Period;<br />
(d)	in terms of Registered Users only, have a UK postal address that matches the billing address for the Payment Card; and<br />
(e)	agree to these terms and conditions.</p>
<p>2.2 We reserve the right to refuse your registration to Cycle Hire and use of a Cycle, in accordance with the provisions of our User Policy.</p>
<h2>Bike Access Period</h2>
<p>3.1 You will be required to purchase a Bike Access Period:<br />
a) when registering as a Registered User, for each Key on your account or
b) to use Cycle Hire as a Casual User, for you and each Additional User
and a Bike Access Fee shall apply to each Bike Access Period purchased.</p>
<p>3.2 The Bike Access Period shall commence:<br />
(a) if you are a Registered User, when you (or an Additional User) use the
Key to undock a Cycle from a Docking Point for the first time. If you have
purchased more than one Key, the Bike Access Period will commence on
first use of each Key; or<br />
(b) as a Casual User, when:<br />
(i) pre-purchasing a Bike Access Period on-line, when you first present
your Payment Card at the Terminal to retrieve any one of the
Release Code(s) to undock a Cycle(s) from a Docking Point(s) for the
first time; or<br />
(ii) registering at the Terminal, when you first present your Payment
Card at the Terminal to purchase a Bike Access Period.</p>
<p>3.3 Your (and each Additional User's) right to use Cycle Hire shall
automatically expire at the end of the relevant Bike Access Period.</p>
<p>3.4 When the Bike Access Period has expired:
<br />
(a) if you are a Registered User, the relevant Key will be unable to undock a
Cycle from a Docking Point, unless and until you purchase a new Bike Access
Period for such Key(s) or you have agreed to Pay As You Pedal; and<br />
(b) if you are a Casual User, you (and your Additional Users) will be unable to
undock a Cycle from a Docking Point, unless and until you purchase a new
Bike Access Period and retrieve a Release Code.</p>
<h2>Pay As You Pedal</h2>
<p>4.1 As a Registered User, you may authorise us to automatically renew the Bike Access Period for one or more Keys on your account for the same Daily or Yearly Bike Access Period that you last purchased in respect of the relevant Key(s) (&quot;Pay As You Pedal&quot;).</p>
<p>4.2 If you selected to Pay As You Pedal, we will deduct the relevant Bike Access Fee(s) for the relevant Key(s), either on the date that:<br />
(a) the Bike Access Period ends during your or an Additional User's use of a Cycle; or<br />
(b) you present the Key(s) at a Docking Point to undock a Cycle following expiry of the previous Bike Access Period.</p>
<h2>Keys and Release Codes</h2>
<p>5.1 If you register as a Registered User, you will be required to purchase a Key for yourself and each Additional User.</p>
<p>5.2 Each Key issued to you:<br />
a) is personal to you;<br />
b) should only be used by you (and your Additional Users) in accordance with the Key Use Policy<br />
c) must be looked after by you with reasonable care; and<br />
d) shall remain our property at all times</p>
<p>5.3 Unless you have agreed to Pay as You Pedal, your (and each Additional User's) Key cannot be used to undock a Cycle from a Docking Point once the Bike Access Period for the relevant Key(s) has expired, unless and until you purchase a new Bike Access Period for such Key(s) and following payment of the relevant Bike Access Fee for you and each Additional User (as applicable).</p>
<h3>Release Codes</h3>
<p>5.4 If you use Cycle Hire as a Casual User, you will be issued with a Release Code upon presentation of your Payment Card at the Terminal each time you (or an Additional User) wish to use a Cycle. The Release Code for each Cycle shall detail the time period that you (or an Additional User) will be able to undock a Cycle from the Docking Point at the Docking Station at which the Release Code was issued. Once that time period has lapsed, you will not be able to release a Cycle using that Release Code.</p>
<h2>Additional Users</h2>
6.1 When purchasing a Bike Access Period, you may purchase a Bike Access
Period for you and (if you are a Casual User) for up to 3 persons or (if
you are a Registered User) for each person with a Key on your account,
to use Cycle Hire during the relevant Bike Access Period,
provided that such persons are:<br />
a) Aged 14 years or over; and<br />
b) Authorised by you to use Cycle Hire, (each person being an Additional User).
<p>6.2 You are responsible for:
<br />
a) Each Additional User and any of their actions when using a
Cycle. This means that you must ensure that each Additional User
complies with these terms and conditions and all other published
requirements of Cycle Hire from time to time and that each
Additional User has due regard to the Tips for Safer Cycling<br />
b) ensuring that each Additional User understands that we may
require certain information about their use of a Cycle, in accordance
with paragraph <a href="#obligations">Your obligations</a> below and<br />
c) all Charges incurred by each Additional User
</p>
<h2>Period of Use and Extra Ride Charges</h2>
<p>7.1 Cycles should not be used for more than 24 consecutive hours (Maximum Period of Use).</p>
<p>7.2 You (and each Additional User) must return the Cycle to a Docking Station and securely dock the Cycle at a docking point prior to the expiry of the Maximum Period of Use.</p>
<p>7.3 The Extra Ride Charges, as set out in paragraph <a href="/corporate/terms-and-conditions/santander-cycles#charges">Charges and payment below</a>, shall vary according to the length of time that you (or an Additional User) have taken a Cycle from a Docking Point for use (Period of Use). The Period of Use for each Cycle shall commence when you (or an Additional User) undock that Cycle from a Docking Point and ends when you (or an Additional User) securely dock the Cycle, and receive a green light, at a Docking Point.</p>
<p>7.4 The Period of Use shall be determined using the data recorded on our systems and that data shall be proof of your (and each Additional User's) Period of Use.</p>
<p>7.5 A time interval, to be determined by us and as defined at www.tfl.gov.uk/cycle-hire, is required between the end of one journey and the commencement of a subsequent journey in order for the subsequent journey to qualify as a separate journey and enable us to calculate the relevant Extra Ride Charges. We reserve the right to prevent you from undocking a Cycle from a Docking Point until this time interval has expired.</p>
<p>7.6 Please note that you only have 120 days from the date that the relevant Charge is collected to either query the Charge or to claim a refund and any queries or claims submitted following the expiry of this period will not be processed or paid.</p>
<h2>Availability of Cycle Hire</h2>
<p>
8.1 We will always try to run a reliable service. Sometimes part or all of Cycle Hire will be unable to operate for reasons beyond our reasonable control. We reserve the right to change the advertised dates and hours of operation of Cycle Hire without giving you prior notice.</p>
<p>8.2 During certain periods, Cycle Hire may be heavily used so we cannot always guarantee to have a:<br />
a) cycle available for use at the Docking Station of your (or an Additional User's) choice or<br />
b) Docking Point available to dock a Cycle at the Docking Station of your (or an Additional User's) choice
</p>
<p>8.3 If you are unable to dock a Cycle(s) at the Docking Station of your choice due to the lack of an available Docking Point(s), you should:<br />
a) present your Payment Card (if you are a Casual User) or Key (if you are a Registered User) at the Terminal at the affected Docking Station and follow the on-screen instructions to receive information of alternative Docking Stations and<br />
b) dock the Cycle(s) at one of the alternative Docking Stations suggested at the Terminal or of your choice<br />
The Terminal will state the maximum period of time that you are allowed in order to dock the Cycle(s) at an alternative Docking Station without incurring any additional Charge.
</p>
<p>8.4 Where we are unable to provide you with a Cycle, you may be eligible for a refund of certain Charges that you have paid us, as determined in accordance with our Refund Policy. In accordance with our Refund Policy, we will not refund any of the Charges that you have paid us for any failure or delay due to an event beyond our reasonable control.</p>
