<p>9.4 If you (or an Additional User) experience any problem with a Cycle during the Period of Use that prevents you (or an Additional User) from continuing to use the Cycle or securely docking a Cycle at an available Docking Point (as indicated by a green light), please contact our Contact Centre. If you (or an Additional User) experience any problem and are able to safely continue to use the Cycle and return it to a Docking Station, please report the problem to us by pressing the &quot;fault&quot; button at the Docking Point when you (or an Additional User) dock the Cycle.</p>
<h2>Public Liability Insurance</h2>
<p>
10.1 We have arranged for the provision of public liability insurance, which insures you (and each Additional User) against liability you (or an Additional User) incur in respect of injury to a third party or accidental damage to the physical property of a third party arising from your (or an Additional User's) use of a Cycle (&quot;Public Liability Insurance&quot;). The Public Liability Insurance cover is limited in scope and amount and subject to various exceptions. For more information about the Public Liability Insurance, see <a href="/corporate/terms-and-conditions/santander-cycles-insurance">Cycle Hire insurance</a>. </p>
<p>10.2 The cost of the Public Liability Insurance is included in the Charges. Due to the way that we have arranged the insurance, it is not possible for you (or an Additional User) to opt out of the Public Liability Insurance.</p>
<p>10.3 It is important to note that, where you (or an Additional User) are eligible to benefit from the Public Liability Insurance in respect of a claim by a third party, you are required to pay (subject to certain exceptions) the excess detailed on our page on <a href="/corporate/terms-and-conditions/santander-cycles-insurance">Cycle Hire insurance</a>. </p>
<p>10.4 While using a Cycle, you (and each Additional User) must comply with these terms and conditions and cycle sensibly in order to avoid any events that could create a claim under the Public Liability Insurance.
</p>
<p>10.5 If you (or an Additional User) are involved in an accident or damage or injury is caused to someone or something while using a Cycle, you (or the Additional User) must:<br />
a) Stop cycling when safe to do so; and <br />
b) telephone the Contact Centre<br />
i) to notify us of the accident and any resulting damage to the Cycle and<br />
ii) for instructions as to who to contact in respect of any claim under the Public Liability Insurance</p>
